From: Chuck Lever <chuck.lever@oracle.com>
Date: Tue, 26 May 2015 11:53:52 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] NFS: Fix size of NFSACL SETACL operations
Git-commit: d683cc49daf7c5afca8cd9654aaa1bf63cdf2ad9
Patch-mainline: v4.2
References: git-fixes

When encoding the NFSACL SETACL operation, reserve just the estimated
size of the ACL rather than a fixed maximum. This eliminates needless
zero padding on the wire that the server ignores.

Fixes: ee5dc7732bd5 ('NFS: Fix "kernel BUG at fs/nfs/nfs3xdr.c:1338!"')
Signed-off-by: Chuck Lever <chuck.lever@oracle.com>
Signed-off-by: Trond Myklebust <trond.myklebust@primarydata.com>
Acked-by: NeilBrown <neilb@suse.com>

---
 fs/nfs/nfs3xdr.c |    2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/fs/nfs/nfs3xdr.c
+++ b/fs/nfs/nfs3xdr.c
@@ -1333,7 +1333,7 @@ static void nfs3_xdr_enc_setacl3args(str
 	if (args->npages != 0)
 		xdr_write_pages(xdr, args->pages, 0, args->len);
 	else
-		xdr_reserve_space(xdr, NFS_ACL_INLINE_BUFSIZE);
+		xdr_reserve_space(xdr, args->len);
 
 	error = nfsacl_encode(xdr->buf, base, args->inode,
 			    (args->mask & NFS_ACL) ?
